<!--template match = paragraph--><p>
DISTRIBUTION. — This species has a very scattered distribution in NW coastal 
Gabon
(around Libreville), coastal 
Republic of Congo
(mouth of Kouilou River), northern 
Angola
, and the north of 
São Tomé
island (
<!--template match = figureCitation--><xref rid="fig-8--132-143-922-939-">Fig. 2</xref>
).
</p>
</tp:treatment-sec>
<!--template match = subSubSection[ancestor::treatment]--><tp:treatment-sec sec-type="biology_ecology">
<!--template match = paragraph--><p>
HABITAT. — 
Littoral
thickets, edge of mangroves, and forest islands in savanna, often associated with rocky outcrops (especially of limestone), 
0-1200 m
in elevation; often gregarious, sometimes even dominant in its habitat.
</p>
<!--template match = paragraph--><p>
PHENOLOGY. — 
Flowers
collected in 
January
, 
March
to 
July
, and 
September
to 
November
, probably all year round; fruits in 
November.
</p>
</tp:treatment-sec>
